content: Seems like a half finished idea. Not much to do really and has nothing to do with DNA. You get essentially random combinations of body parts.

My 4yo loved it then and still plays it now that she's 6, but she would 
prefer the opening game (matching chromosomes) to be longer/make 
reappearances and to have more control over the effects - sometimes she 
REALLY wants her monster to have blue legs...)
This is so awesome anyone looking for apps should totally install it.
I love this game but it lags on my phone
I was looking for this game fror ages like 2 yrs
Is there a setting to turn the sound off?
replyContent:
Hello Rachel,

in DNA Play there is no such setting, because the music and sound effects are an integral part of the experience. Many interactions & animations, especially the dance sequences, would make little sense without the music. However, there is the option to mute the app through the device's volume buttons.

Regards,
The Avokiddo Team

content: Did not think my 4yo would like it, but I was proved completely wrong. Watching the animations has her laughing no end.
It wouldn't let me swipe to the mouth feature
replyContent: Hi Jessica, in order to swipe to the mouth puzzle you first need to complete all previous puzzles (torso, head, eyes). If this is done and you're still unable to move forward, please contact us through our website so we can help you. If your issue is solved, we would appreciate it if you would consider updating your review and rating. Thanks!
